== English ==
=== Pronunciation ===
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛst|-ɛst]]

=== Verb ===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|divest||}}
# {{archaic}} To remove all of one's [[clothing]]; to [[strip]].
# {{cattag|obsolete|figurative}} To [[strip]], [[deprive]] or [[dispossess]] oneself of something (such as a [[right]], [[passion]], [[privilege]] or [[prejudice]]).
#: ''I '''divested''' his right to free speech.''
#: ''When I wake up, I make a point to '''divest''' myself all of my prejudices, ready to start the day.''

==== Synonyms ====
* (''remove one's clothing'') [[strip]] [[strip off]], [[strip down]], [[unclothe]], [[disrobe]]

==== Antonyms ====
